<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD (Reconditioning) - VALVE
        GUIDES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="12">
        <title>VALVE GUIDES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a nylon brush, soap and water, clean the valve guide bores in the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Blow out any residue with filtered compressed air.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using an appropriate valve guide bore gauge or a telescoping gauge and micrometer, check
                    for proper guide bore diameter (see
                    <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350301.xml" xrefid="hl4350301">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>),
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350336">3.36</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace guides having bore diameters, tapers and/or run-out beyond specified limits.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>VALVE GUIDES ARE CAST INTO THE CYLINDER HEAD AND MUST BE DRILLED OUT TO INSTALL SERVICE
                            GUIDES.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal and Replacement</title>
            <para>Use
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4157</emph>
                Valve Guide Service Tools.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With cylinder head mounted in a holding fixture or on wood blocks, place the bushing
                    plate over the guide to be serviced. Use the two threaded rods, the two nut and plate assemblies and
                    the bushing plate.
                    <emph type="bold">DO NOT</emph>
                    tighten at this time. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350337">3.37</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the aligning tool through the hole in the bushing plate and into the valve guide
                    in the cylinder head. The hole in the bushing plate is now concentric with the valve guide (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350338">3.38</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the nuts holding the bushing plate.</para>
                <figure id="ef4350336" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11070" filename="../figcg1/cg11070.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.36 Checking Valve Guide Bore</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350337" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11071" filename="../figcg1/cg11071.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.37 Bushing Plate Mounted Over Valve Guide</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350338" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11111" filename="../figcg1/cg11111.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.38 Aligning Tool in Bushing Plate and Valve Guide</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>REQUIRED TOOLS:</para>
                        <para>VALVE GUIDE SERVICE TOOLS ZTSE4157 CONSISTS OF:</para>
                        <table id="et4350306">
                            <tgroup cols="2">
                                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="72p"/>
                                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="150p"/>
                                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="S1T2"/>
                                <thead>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>QUANTITY</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>DESCRIPTION</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>BUSHING PLATE</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>2</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>THREADED RODS W/NUTS</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>ALIGNING TOOL</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>DRILL BUSHING 19/32 in.</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>CORE DRILL</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>PILOT</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>END MILL</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>REAMER BUSHING</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>REAMER</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>GUIDE DRIVER</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <entry colname="1">
                                            <para>1</para>
                                        </entry>
                                        <entry colname="2">
                                            <para>FINISH REAMER</para>
                                        </entry>
                                    </row>
                                </tbody>
                            </tgroup>
                        </table>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the aligning tool (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350338">3.38</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) and insert the 19/32 in. drill bushing (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350339">3.39</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a 1/2 in. electric drill with the drive adapter installed in the chuck, drill out
                    the cast valve guide, refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350340">3.40</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Lubricate with cutting oil during drilling.</para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>DRILL SPEED SHOULD NOT EXCEED 600 RPM.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350339" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11112" filename="../figcg1/cg11112.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.39 Drill Bushing in Valve Guide</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350340" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11086" filename="../figcg1/cg11086.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.40 Drilling Cast Valve Guide from Cylinder Head; Using Drive Adapter and 1/2" Drill
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the 19/32 in. core drill into the drill bushing. Deburr valve guide bore. Refer
                    to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350341">3.41</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the core drill and bushing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the cylinder head over to mill the remains of the cast guide on the top of the
                    cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the pilot to the end mill. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350342">3.42</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mill until guide bore is flush with spring seat. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350343">3.43</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the cylinder head over to the combustion chamber side.</para>
                <figure id="ef4350341" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11072" filename="../figcg1/cg11072.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.41 Core Drill Used to Deburr Valve Guide Bore</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350342" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11073" filename="../figcg1/cg11073.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.42 Milling Valve Guide Bores (Top View of Cylinder Head)</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350343" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11141" filename="../figcg1/cg11141.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.43 Guide Bore Flush with Spring Seat</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the reamer bushing into the bushing plate. (See
                    <emph type="bold">Note</emph>.) Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350338">3.38</hotlnk>.
                    </emph>
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Refer to Section 3 for valve guide insert bore diameter specification.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Dip the first three inches of the reamer in cutting oil and install it into the reamer
                    bushing. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350344">3.44</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the drive adapter to a 1/2 in. drill and ream through the cylinder head. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350345">3.45</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the reamer and bushing.</para>
                <figure id="ef4350344" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11142" filename="../figcg1/cg11142.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.44 Set Up for Reaming Valve Guide Insert Bore in Cylinder Head</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350345" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11143" filename="../figcg1/cg11143.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.45 Reaming Valve Guide Bore in Cylinder Head</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position a new valve guide on the valve guide driver. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350346">3.46</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate valve guides and bore with clean engine oil prior to assembly.
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the valve guide through the bushing plate and drive the guide into the head until
                    the driver stops on the bushing plate (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350347">3.47</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Freezing the valve guide will assist in installation.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4350346" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11144" filename="../figcg1/cg11144.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.46 Positioning Valve Guide onto Driver</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350347" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11145" filename="../figcg1/cg11145.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.47 Installing Valve Guide Into Cylinder Head</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bushing plate and use the valve guide finishing reamer (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_52.xml" xrefid="ef4350348">3.48</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) to finish the new valve guide insert bore. (See
                    <emph type="bold">Note</emph>.)
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Refer to Section 3, for valve guide bore diameter specification.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
